  "description": "Installation of replacement doors/windows to front elevation",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed shopfront and replacement windows/doors, by reason of its design, appearance and use of materials, would result in an incongruous and visually intrusive form of development, which fails to harmonise with the architectural composition of the original property and is detrimental to the character, appearance and visual amenities of the streetscene, and fails to preserve or enhance the character or appearance of the wider Harefield Conservation Area. The The proposal is therefore contrary to Policies BE1 and HE1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part One Strategic Policies, Policies DMHB1, DMHB4 and DMHB 12 of the Hillingdon Local Plan Part  2 - Development Management Policies (2020), Policies HC1, D1 and D4 of the London Plan (2021) and the National Planning Framework (2021).",
    "The proposed development by virtue of the new doors and access arrangement would fail to ensure that adequate provision would be provided to meet the needs of people with disabilities, and represents a downgrade on the existing accessibility for wheelchair users. The proposed development therefore conflicts with Policy D5 of the London Plan (2021) and the National Planning Policy Framework (2021)."
  ],
